$ Perl substitution: replace and assign

In order to assign the changed value of a → development/languages/Perl/functions/s[substition] to a new variable without changing the original value, the initialization
of the new variable along with the assignment must be put into parantheses: `(my $new_var = $orig_var) =~ s/.../.../;`

